{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, like natural language, images are represented as sequences of discrete tokens obtained by an image tokenizer.",
    "Transformers that use health images as input are out of the scope of this paper.",
    "A review on this subject can be seen in He et al. (2022).",
    "The input embedding layer is a type of lookup table that contains vectorial representations of input data (e.g., each term of the vocabulary).",
    "This layer is essential because transformers process vectors of continuous values like any other machine learning algorithm."
  ]
}